Halve, peel and chop the @onion{1}(peeled and chopped) into small pieces. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}). Halve the @lime{1}. Drain and rinse the @black beans{1}(drained and rinsed) in a #colander{}.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{}. Once hot, add the @British beef mince{240%g} and cook until browned, ~{4-5%minutes}. Use a #spoon{} to break it up as it cooks. Add the onion and cook, stirring regularly, until the onion has softened, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Preheat your #oven{} to 200°C. Once the onion has softened, add the garlic, @chipotle paste{20} and @tomato puree{30} and cook, stirring, for ~{1%minute}. Add the @BBQ sauce{32} with the @water{150%ml} and the black beans. Season with @salt{} and @black pepper{}. Bring to a simmer and cook, stirring occasionally, until thickened, ~{12-15%minutes}.

Slice lengthways into the @avocado{1}. Once you reach the stone, turn the avocado around to cut it in half. Twist each half and pull it apart. Remove the stone then scoop out the flesh onto a #cutting board{}. Finely chop into small pieces then pop into a #bowl{} and squeeze over half of the lime juice. Season with @salt{} and @black pepper{}. Carefully mix together then set aside.

Lay the @plain taco tortillas{6} on a #baking sheet{} (3 each) and pop in the oven to warm through, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Taste the beef mixture and add more salt and pepper if you like. Divide the taco wraps between plates. Top with the chipotle beef and diced avocado. Enjoy!